    <definition xml:id="definitionboundedsequence">
        <p>
            A sequence <m>\{x_n\}</m> is <em>bounded</em> if there are real numbers <m>b_u, b_{\ell}</m> such that <me>b_{\ell}\leq x_n \leq b_u</me> for every <m>n</m>?
        </p>
    </definition>
    
    <activity>
        <introduction>
            <p>
                Consider the sequence <m>\left\{\displaystyle \frac{(-1)^n}{n}\right\}_{n=1}^\infty.</m>
            </p>
        </introduction>
        <task>
            <p>
                Is there a <m>b_u</m> such that <m>x_n\leq b_u</m> for every <m>n</m>?  If so, what would be one such <m>b_u</m>?
            </p>
        </task>
        
        <task>
            <p>
                Is there a <m>b_\ell</m> such that <m>b_\ell x_n</m> for every <m>n</m>?  If so, what would be one such <m>b_\ell</m>?
            </p>
        </task>
        
        <task>
            <p>
                Is <m>\left\{\displaystyle \frac{(-1)^n}{n}\right\}_{n=1}^\infty</m> bounded?
            </p>
        </task>
    </activity>
    
    
